main event: In August 1963, two individuals observed four bright, disc-like objects traveling south in Plainview, New York.
interesting points: The objects appeared highly reflective and shiny., They were reported to be traveling at considerable speed., The witnesses described the objects as silent with no sound detected., The sighting lasted for about 10 seconds., The report concluded with insufficient data for evaluation due to the lack of physical evidence and photographs.
witness description: individuals who reported the sighting to the U.S. Air Force
